1. Create the dashboard
In Grafana:
Dashboards
→ New
→ New dashboard
→ Add visualization
→ Prometheus
Save it as:
Product Service Performance
Set:
Time range: Last 15 minutes
Auto refresh: 5s during testing, 30s normally
2. Create the method variable
Open:
Dashboard settings
→ Variables
→ Add variable
Configure:
Name: method
Label: HTTP Method
Type: Query
Data source: Prometheus
Query:
label_values(
  http_server_requests_seconds_count{job="product-service"},
  method
)
If your Grafana uses the structured variable editor, select:
Query type: Label values
Label: method
Metric:
http_server_requests_seconds_count

Label filter:
job = product-service
Options:
Multi-value: On
Include All: On
Custom all value: .*
Refresh: On dashboard load
Sort: Alphabetical
3. Create the endpoint variable
Add another variable:
Name: uri
Label: Endpoint
Type: Query
Data source: Prometheus
Query:
label_values(
  http_server_requests_seconds_count{
    job="product-service",
    method=~"$method"
  },
  uri
)
Structured editor equivalent:
Query type: Label values
Label: uri
Metric:
http_server_requests_seconds_count

Label filters:
job = product-service
method =~ $method
Options:
Multi-value: On
Include All: On
Custom all value: .*
Refresh: On dashboard load
Sort: Alphabetical
Place the variables in this order:
method → uri
Select:
HTTP Method: GET
Endpoint: /api/products
to begin.
4. Optional status variable
Add:
Name: status
Label: HTTP Status
Type: Query
Query:
label_values(
  http_server_requests_seconds_count{
    job="product-service",
    method=~"$method",
    uri=~"$uri"
  },
  status
)
Options:
Multi-value: On
Include All: On
Custom all value: .*
Default: All
Most performance panels should include all status codes. Use this variable mainly for investigation.
5. Confirm the available labels
Create a temporary Prometheus query:
count by (method, uri, status) (
  http_server_requests_seconds_count{
    job="product-service"
  }
)
Confirm that it returns route values such as:
/api/products
/api/products/{id}
/api/products/active
If the job value is different, check:
label_values(http_server_requests_seconds_count, job)
Then replace product-service in the queries with the actual job label.
