7. Panel: Average latency
Query:
sum(
  rate(http_server_requests_seconds_sum{
    job="product-service",
    method=~"$method",
    uri=~"$uri"
  }[$__rate_interval])
)
/
clamp_min(
  sum(
    rate(http_server_requests_seconds_count{
      job="product-service",
      method=~"$method",
      uri=~"$uri"
    }[$__rate_interval])
  ),
  0.000001
)
Settings:
Title:
Average Latency — $method $uri

Visualization:
Time series

Unit:
Time → seconds (s)

Min:
0

Decimals:
Auto
The metric returns seconds. Grafana will automatically display smaller values in milliseconds.
Thresholds:
Base: Green
0.3 seconds: Yellow
0.5 seconds: Red
If the Grafana threshold editor displays values in milliseconds after unit conversion, verify the raw query value first. The PromQL result itself is in seconds.
